i> ‘friendly, good-humoured’). The initial vowel began to be lost as early as the 12th century (the same woman is referred to as both <i>Mabilia</i> and <i>Amabilia</i> in a document of  1185 ), but a short vowel in the resulting first syllable was standard, giving a rhyme with <i>babble</i>, until the 19th century, when people began to pronounce the name to rhyme with <i>table</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ouvri 'Rabel' de Saint-Omer was born in 1002, in Saint-Omer, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Lambert Ier DE SAINT-OMER, was 28 and his mother, Béatrix, was 13. He had at least 2 sons with Ghislaine de Ghent. He died about 1088, at the age of 87."},"et":{"1002–about 1088":"1002–umbes 1088","1002–1088":"1002–1088","1030–1059":"1030–1059","1038–1094":"1038–1094","1053–1089":"1053–1089","0975–1063":"0975–1063","0989–1035":"0989–1035","1088":"1088","1053":"1053","1063":"1063","1030":"1030","1094":"1094","0975":"0975","29 mai 1035":"29. mai 1035","1038":"1038","1059":"1059","1002":"1002","1035":"1035","1089":"1089","about 1026":"umbes 1026","0989":"0989","about 1053":"umbes 1053","about 1088":"umbes 1088","Picardie, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Saint-Omer, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Saint-Omer, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Guînes, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France":"Guînes, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Saint-Omer, Calvados, Normandie, France":"Saint-Omer, Calvados, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Roucy, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Roucy, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1002–about 1088":"1002–noin 1088","1002–1088":"1002–1088","1030–1059":"1030–1059","1038–1094":"1038–1094","1053–1089":"1053–1089","0975–1063":"0975–1063","0989–1035":"0989–1035","1088":"1088","1053":"1053","1063":"1063","1030":"1030","1094":"1094","0975":"0975","29 mai 1035":"29. toukokuuta 1035","1038":"1038","1059":"1059","1002":"1002","1035":"1035","1089":"1089","about 1026":"noin 1026","0989":"0989",